childNodes.textContent: Adam Christopher David Rooney, born on April 21, 1988, is an Irish professional footballer who plays as a striker for National League North club Hereford, where he is also the assistant manager.
Here's a summary of his career:
He has played for Stoke City.
He had loan spells at Yeovil Town, Chesterfield, and Bury.
He was a regular first-team member for Inverness Caledonian Thistle.
He played for Birmingham City and had a loan spell at Swindon Town.
He spent four and a half seasons with Aberdeen.
He returned to England to sign for Salford City, where he gained promotion to the Football League.
He signed with Solihull Moors on a contract until May 2022.
There is also another Adam Rooney who is a company director and brand manager at Tackle Guru.

node.textContent: Adam Christopher David Rooney, born on April 21, 1988, is an Irish professional footballer who plays as a striker for National League North club Hereford, where he is also the assistant manager.
Here's a summary of his career:
He has played for Stoke City.
He had loan spells at Yeovil Town, Chesterfield, and Bury.
He was a regular first-team member for Inverness Caledonian Thistle.
He played for Birmingham City and had a loan spell at Swindon Town.
He spent four and a half seasons with Aberdeen.
He returned to England to sign for Salford City, where he gained promotion to the Football League.
He signed with Solihull Moors on a contract until May 2022.
There is also another Adam Rooney who is a company director and brand manager at Tackle Guru.

node.textContent: Adam Christopher David Rooney, born on April 21, 1988, is an Irish professional footballer who plays as a striker for National League North club Hereford, where he is also the assistant manager.
Here's a summary of his career:
He has played for Stoke City.
He had loan spells at Yeovil Town, Chesterfield, and Bury.
He was a regular first-team member for Inverness Caledonian Thistle.
He played for Birmingham City and had a loan spell at Swindon Town.
He spent four and a half seasons with Aberdeen.
He returned to England to sign for Salford City, where he gained promotion to the Football League.
He signed with Solihull Moors on a contract until May 2022.
There is also another Adam Rooney who is a company director and brand manager at Tackle Guru.

childNodes.textContent: Adam Christopher David Rooney, born on April 21, 1988, is an Irish professional footballer who plays as a striker for National League North club Hereford, where he is also the assistant manager.
Here's a summary of his career:
He has played for Stoke City.
He had loan spells at Yeovil Town, Chesterfield, and Bury.
He was a regular first-team member for Inverness Caledonian Thistle.
He played for Birmingham City and had a loan spell at Swindon Town.
He spent four and a half seasons with Aberdeen.
He returned to England to sign for Salford City, where he gained promotion to the Football League.
He signed with Solihull Moors on a contract until May 2022.
There is also another Adam Rooney who is a company director and brand manager at Tackle Guru.
